I have made this recipe numerous times and while this recipe has pretty much all the components of being delicious. I have changed this recipe a bit over time to suit my familys taste. Most all reviews say to double the sauce, I couldn't agree more. In fact, I have that written down on my recipe and then crossed out with triple or quadruple the sauce for 4 people, but we love the sauce so that may be excessive for most. I now use onions instead of shallots, mainly because I never have them on hand. While I use the whipping cream we also add in almost an equal amount of sour cream. Also, we use about 3 times the dijon and we don't add the dill at all. I do use the cognac, but if I don't have it on hand also use bourbon. This is one of our all time favorite meals now. It is funny how people make the comment that if you change a recipe, you can't really rate it...well that is true to a point. While the first time I made this dish exactly by the directions it was just ok, but now that I have the "base" recipe and have tweaked it to our liking it is a family favorite. Also, I agree with other posters, next time I am adding in some worcestershire sauce too.

