I offer this review cautiously because I also made changes in-line with other comments: 1 1/2 lb sirloin, substituted onion & garlic for shallots, sour cream for creme fraiche, used 1/3 cup brandy, added 3 T Worcestershire, xtra Dijon, and 1/4 tsp nutmeg. My comment is mostly about the dill: I found that dill is called for in other Stroganoff recipes. Instead of eliminating it, I cut the amount by 2/3. It added a very nice, subtle background flavor. The end result was excellent. Next time, I'll bump the dill up to 1/2 that called for; and, I am not a huge fan of dill because (IMO) it can easily over- power. I've rated the basic recipe a 3 and will make it again; but, adding the flavors noted pushes it to 3.5. Will also try Cremini next time. The biggest change I made was adding Worcestershire; and, I think the dish needed it. But, this substantially alters the flavor and makes my review of this recipe unfair.

