The variations stated in this recipe from the more classic version of the dish are very satisfying. I would make it again with no changes. I must also state though that there have been some very questionable substitutions to this recipe. To be blunt-if you are reviewing a recipe-please review THE recipe. It's one thing if you believe that a particular ingredient is not to your liking or the cooking time didn't work for you. It's entirely different when you review a recipe and state that you substituted 4 ingredients, several of which are an integral part and then proceed to review/critique. One example would be to state that you substituted lamb for beef. Sorry, but it's called beef stroganoff. Its only a matter of fairness to the person/editor/writer who submitted the recipe.

