Rating: 3
Yep, this was fabulous. After reading all other reviews and looking at what I had in the cupboard: added a clove of minced garlic, used 1/2 button mushrooms, 1/2 baby portabellos and--I think this is at the root of other cooks' variants--used a mixture of sour cream, marscapone (!) and skim milk instead of whipping cream. This is the step that determines the amount/thickness of sauce (along with the amount of stock you use). Marscapone was an odd choice, but I had it in the fridge. Next time, I'll use something looser for this step and add milk to reach the consistency of sauce desired. (Made it with tenderloin; will try other meats when not feeling so flush!)

