Rating: 4
This is pretty much the stroganoff recipe for which I've been searching, with just the right flavors and richness. I did make a few modifications: only used half the amount of beef called for, used equal parts white, baby bella, and shiitake mushrooms, used about half of a small yellow onion in addition to the shallots, used sour cream plus a little bit of heavy cream in place of creme fraiche, and used regular brandy in place of cognac. I served the dish over extra broad egg noodles tossed with butter and fresh parsley (the noodles are a must for me), and thought it was excellent. I will say that the amount of sauce the recipe made was barely enough for the 1.25 lbs. of beef that I used, and certainly wouldn't have been enough had I used the full 2.5 lbs. called for. I'll probably increase the sauce ingredients by 50% next time, still using only 1.25 lbs. of beef. Finally, I echo the others who have stressed *not* skimping on the quality of the meat; the extreme tenderness of the beef tenderloin is crucial to the finished product.

