A very fine meal by all respects, it pleased both myself a self professed gourmet eater, and my boyfriend a self professed "meat and potatoes and keep it simple" eater. Based on review comments and past experience, I used only 1 lb of beef, and about 9oz of egg noodles. Otherwise I followed all ingredient quantities and cooking time instructions to a tee, and it came out a very well balanced dish serving about 3-4 adults. 2-1/2 lbs of meat would be way too much, and I always find epicurious recipies are too heavy on pasta or noodle quantities. I also used rib eye sliced very thin, because tenderloin was a bit pricey for a weeknight dinner, and sherry in place of cognac since I didn't have any on hand. Although I'm sure the tenderloin would be more tender than rib eye, I do no think the dish dramatically suffered from my substitutions. The dill is a very key flavor to the dish, and is delicious, so it should not be left out, unless you absolutely cannot stand the taste of dill. Fresh parsley is also a nice addition.

