Rating: 4
The best stroganoff recipe ever. I also add one or two T of soy sauce to add a bit more flavor. If you want to thicken the sauce, add a bit of a roux. In a small pan, add two or three tablespoons of butter. When it begins to get hot, add a couple of tablespoons of flour, and whisk until it follows the whisk around the pan. Add stock to thin out roux until it thickens. Add by dropfulls to stroganoff until you reach desired consistency.

