Rating: 3
I used this recipe as a base and then counter-checked it with one of same name in my "Hungarian Ladies of the Lutheran Church" cookbook (circa 1959!) Basically revised as follows: melted one stick butter, added 3-4 large portobellos chopped into large chunks and one large chopped onion. Cook for about 15 minutes. Add beef broth (I also had some duck broth which was VERY good and rich) and the cognac or burgundy. Leave out the mustard, use sour cream and parsley instead of whipping cream and dill. Came out EXCELLENT!

