Rating: 3
Made 3 times before it turned out to my taste. 1st, followed exactly and didn't like it. End adjustments: Used end-cut tenderloin (much cheaper, same cut!), saute 3 cloves garlic with shallots, add 1 tsp salt, 1/4 tsp cayenne pepper and 1/2 tsp Hot Hungarian paprika w/beef broth, add cornstarch to thicken before creme fraiche, Dijon overwhelmed flavors, omitted it, was the very ingredient throwing everything else off. Great served with homemade spaetzel and sweet-sour red cabbage, or just over rice. Creme fraiche is a fun idea, but sour cream just as good and easier. Add beef very last minute for tenderness and not to overcook. Query: Since when is rating a recipe you use as a base, but find you need to change it "rating your own recipe"? Lighten up! Warsaw Cook: What is "fresh" stroganoff? Enlighten us.

