A very pleasing Sunday. For what it's worth: I think it's very important to use beef tenderloin, cut across the grain. A cheaper cut would not work as well. I used three large shallots and thought the recipe needed every bit of them. I used a whole can of beef broth and a whole cup of sour cream, then reduced about ten to fifteen minutes. That ended up with the right amount of sauce, but needed a teaspoon of corn starch in a teaspoon of water to thicken it up...with no negative consequences. Finally, I cooked my moodles in salted water and added a big handfull of fresh chopped parsley with the butter before serving. Served with a simple salad of bibb lettuce and sliced tomatoes with a light vinegrette on the side.

