The past couple years my Beef Stroganoff recipe seemed to be lacking something...bland, so I tried this recipe. The dijon helped, but I ended up adding some cayenne pepper as well. I think the spicier we go, the more bland the old favorites begin to taste. We were recently wondering what happened to the 'hot' in hot Chinese mustard? We were also wondering what happened to the heat in jalepeno peppers? I don't think the 'hot' in the mustard or jalepeno peppers has decreased insomuch as our tolerance for heat has increased. I don't know if that makes any sense? If it makes sense to you then you will understand why the cayenne pepper helped the dish.

