Rating: 3
This finished product was actually quite good. I did 1 1/2 times the ingredients for the sauce after reading the reviews. I found the cooking times indicated to be correct. For the beef, make sure to slice it as thinly as possible, then DO NOT salt it before cooking. It will draw the moisture out and make it tougher. Season afterwords while it's resting. Also start with a very hot pan so that the meat can sear, rather then saute. I didn't have creme fraiche handy so I did use sour cream with good results. If your sauce was runny, make sure to cook the mushrooms au sec, then REDUCE the stock and cognac by applying higher heat for the 14 mins. You shouldn't have to dredge the meat in order to thicken the sauce! The dill is essential for the recipe as well as chopped parsley.

